headlines.description: — James Harden refused to stump for an all All-Star bid. After another standout game in a Philadelphia 76ers win in which he fell one rebound shy of a triple-double, Harden can let his statistics sell his candidacy.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Harden double-doubles lift 76ers past Magic 105-94

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 42 points and 10 assists, Anfernee Simons added 26 points and the Portland Trail Blazers rallied to beat the Memphis Grizzlies 122-112 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard, Simons lead Trail Blazers past Grizzlies, 122-112

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 31 points and had nine rebounds and the Boston Celtics rolled to a 139-96 win over the short-handed Brooklyn Nets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 31, Celtics sizzle in 139-96 rout of Nets

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Eric Gordon had a season-high 25 points and rookie Tari Eason added career-high 20 to lead the Houston Rockets to a 112-106 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon, rookie Eason help Rockets defeat Thunder 112-106

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — D'Angelo Russell scored 14 of his 29 points in the fourth quarter, Anthony Edwards took over in overtime after Russell fouled out and the Minnesota Timberwolves outlasted the Golden State Warriors 119-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell, Edwards help Timberwolves beat Warriors in OT

events.name: Sacramento Kings at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored a season-high 34 points and had 11 rebounds and the Sacramento Kings beat San Antonio 119-109 on Wednesday night, handing the beleaguered Spurs their seventh straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis' double-double helps Kings power past Spurs 119-109

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 28 points and 13 rebounds and Mike Conley added a three-point play and two clutch free throws in the closing minutes to lift the Utah Jazz to a 131-128 win over the Toronto Raptors on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen, Conley power Jazz to 131-128 win over Raptors

headlines.description: — Trae Young rose up for a 3-pointer in the second half that left his hands way too hard, hurtling toward the basket before slamming off the backboard and through the hoop.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 21 points, Hawks roll past Suns 132-100
